47: /**
48:  * The {@link CheckpointBarrierTracker} keeps track of what checkpoint barriers have been received
49:  * from which input channels. Once it has observed all checkpoint barriers for a checkpoint ID, it
50:  * notifies its listener of a completed checkpoint.
51:  *
52:  * <p>Unlike the {@link SingleCheckpointBarrierHandler}, the BarrierTracker does not block the input
53:  * channels that have sent barriers, so it cannot be used to gain "exactly-once" processing
54:  * guarantees. It can, however, be used to gain "at least once" processing guarantees.
55:  *
56:  * <p>NOTE: This implementation strictly assumes that newer checkpoints have higher checkpoint IDs.
57:  */
